definition.value: A carboxamide consisting of a 1-hydroxydodecan-2-yl moiety linked via nitrogen to tetracosanamide. A ceramide mimetic, it is composed of a saturated C12-sphingosine mimetic and lignoceric acid (C24:0).
Any compound that mimics the activity of a ceramide, e.g. by inducing tumor cell death or suppression.
An organic anion that is the conjugate base of hispidin resulting from the deprotonation of the 4-hydroxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
An inorganic calcium salt having silicate as the counterion.
A calcium salt that lacks C-H bonds
An organic calcium salt of stearic acid. It is a component of some lubricants and surfactants.
A magnesium salt that lacks C-H bonds
A magnesium salt with C-H bonds
A magnesium salt with C-H bonds
Any  amino alcohol that is propan-2-ol substituted by an amino group at position 1.
A phosphate salt that lacks C-H bonds
An inorganic potassium salt that is the tripotassium salt of phosphoric acid.
A phosphate salt with C-H bonds
A potassium salt that lacks C-H bonds
Any glycosphingolipid designed and synthesized for the purposes of research.
An artificial glycosphingolipid composed of the ceramide mimetic C12L (CHEBI:190285) bound to a 6'-sialyl LacNAc [alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->6)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-D-GlcNAc] oligosaccharide via a beta-linkage.

An artificial glycosphingolipid composed of the ceramide mimetic C12L (CHEBI:190285) bound to a sialyl Lewis(x) [alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-[alpha-L-Fuc-(1->3)]-D-GlcNAc] oligosaccharide via a beta-linkage.
An artificial glycosphingolipid composed of the ceramide mimetic C12L (CHEBI:190285) bound to a Lewis(x) [beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-[alpha-L-Fuc-(1->3)]-D-GlcNAc] oligosaccharide via a beta-linkage.
A haloalkane that is bromoethane substituted by chlorine at position 2.
